what is architecture of splunk?
Splunk's architecture is a distributed system designed for collecting, indexing, 
searching, and analyzing large volumes of machine-generated data, especially logs
in SOC environments.
forwarder 
gather logs from servers, apps, or networks.��
Indexers: Receive data, parse it into searchable events, store in repositories
Search Heads: User interface for running queries (SPL language), generating reports/dashboards, 
SOC interview, mention that Splunk (or SIEM tools) generally ingests logs from
network devices, servers/endpoints, security appliances, applications, and cloud services



How do you identify a phishing email?
By checking sender domain, suspicious links, urgent language, attachments, and header 
anomalies.

Urgent Language = subject line 
Words like "immediate action required," "account suspension," or "limited time offer"
create panic to bypass caution.

Attachments
Unexpected files, especially .exe, .zip, or macros-enabled docs, may contain malware—scan
or avoid opening

Header Anomalies
Mismatched sender domains instead of@accenture @acccenture.com , unusual IP origins
(e.g., foreign servers for local banks), or spoofed "From" fields visible in email headers.
What do you check in email headers?

Return-Path, Received chain, SPF/DKIM/DMARC results mstoolbox madhe shodhata yet ,
sender IP, and domain mismatch.
रिटर्न पाथ (Return-Path)
ईमेल डिलिव्हर न झाल्यास बाऊन्स मेसेज कुठे पाठवायचे हे सांगणारा हेडर; फसवणूक असल्यास तो संशयास्पद असू शकतो. 

रिटर्न पाथ कसे तपासावे
Gmail मध्ये: ईमेल उघडा > तीन बिंदू (⋮) वर क्लिक > "Show original" निवडा > नवीन टॅबमध्ये "Return-Path"
शोधा. Outlook मध्ये: ईमेलवर राइट-क्लिक > "View message source".

रिसीव्ह्ड चेन कसे तपासावे
तेच "Show original" किंवा "View source" मध्ये "Received:" लाइन शोधा – ईमेलची सर्व्हरची यादी दिसेल, वरच्या IP पहिल्या असतात.

�रिसीव्ह्ड चेन (Received Chain)
ईमेल कुठून-कुठून पाठवले गेले याची यादी; प्रत्येक स्टेपमधील आयपी आणि सर्व्हर तपासून खरा मिळालेला का नाही ते ओळखा.

Spf/dkim/dmarc kase check karave
ईमेल हेडरमध्ये (Gmail: ⋮ > Show original) "Authentication-Results" हेडर शोधा – तिथे spf=pass/fail,
dkim=pass/fail, dmarc=pass/fail असे रिझल्ट दिसतात.
Mstoolbox 
कसे करावे:
mxtoolbox.com वर जा > Domain name टाका (जसे bankofindia.com) > SPF/DKIM/DMARC लिंक क्लिक
करा – पास/फेल रिझल्ट लगेच दिसतात. ईमेल विश्लेषणासाठी Email Deliverability Test करा.
SPF (Sender Policy Framework)SPF verifies if the sending mail server IP is authorized 
             for the domain via DNS TXT record.�
Example: v=spf1 ip4:192.0.2.0/24 -all blocks unauthorized servers
.DKIM (DomainKeys Identified Mail)DKIM adds cryptographic signature to email headers
            proving authenticity and integrity.�
Example: Receiving server checks signature matches sender's public key in DNS.
DMARC (Domain-based Message Authentication, Reporting & Conformance)DMARC combines 
SPF+DKIM results with policy (none/quarantine/reject) for failed emails.�
Example: v=DMARC1; p=reject; rua=mailto:reports@domain.com rejects fakes, sends reports.

What is difference between URL and domain 
Domain- core address part like example.com. Means identify the owner 
URL: Full web address including protocol https://example.com/login/fake,"

Credential Harvesting Links
Links directing to fake login pages mimicking trusted sites 
(e.g., bank or email portals) to steal usernames and passwords

Spear phishing vs phishing?
Phishing is mass attack; spear phishing is targeted and personalized.

BEC म्हणजे Business Email Compromise.
It's a cybercrime where attackers impersonate executives, vendors, or trusted
contacts via spoofed emails to trick employees into authorizing wire transfers, 
sharing sensitive data

SOC मधील BEC म्हणजे व्यवसाय ईमेल फसवणूक (Business Email Compromise). हल्लेखोर CEO किंवा
विक्रेत्याचा ईमेल बनावून कर्मचाऱ्यांना पैसे हस्तांतरित किंवा गोपनीय माहिती देण्यास फसवतात
attackers get information about the senior targeted employee and spoof email and in 
this way attackers trick user by sending the emails 

How attackers bypass email filters?
Using lookalike domains, URL shorteners, encrypted attachments, and social engineering.
Email filters are automated systems in email services like Gmail or Outlook that scan
incoming messages to detect and block spam, phishing, or malicious content based on rules





